            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-06-06T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-06-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="834" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d834">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">834.00/6–347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Paraguay</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-06-06T15:00:00-04:00">June 6, 1947—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>152. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 299 June 3, 6 PM and 300, 301 June
                    4, 10 AM and noon.<note n="35" xml:id="d834fn1">Telegrams 299 and 301 not
                        printed.</note> Fol for your own <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss>: No
                    approach made to date by Brazilian Govt but shd matter be raised Dept wd not at
                    this juncture favor any action that might be construed as pressure by this Govt
                    on Morínigo Admin to accept mediation.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Rio as 591 Montevideo as 192 <gloss target="#t_BA1">BAires</gloss> as
                    485.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
